show_title: GM Farcaster ep203 Thursday January 16, 2025 with @humpty and @sahil
text:
The first ever channel token powered by @openrank was just launched!

/cryptosapiens launched $CABAL (0x0b56fcfC1c1e9Dcc1Db8e61C65283070F02c76C6) as a novel way to reward meaningful engagement on Farcaster.

Earn tokens by participating actively‚Äîcast your insights, share your onchain creations, and engage with the community through likes, recasts, and thoughtful comments. Your contributions fuel a vibrant creator economy, and this token is our way of giving back.

1 billion tokens were created. 50% were locked into LP; the other 50% was allocated as rewards for active channel participants over 3 years.

5% of that allocation was airdropped just moments ago. Allocation was calculated using OpenRank and issued based on activity over the past 60 days.

25 Million CABAL were sent to 245 channel members. You can claim using the frame below.

For more info check OpenRank docs, and Dexscreener linked in the comments below.

https://cura.openrank.com/frames/cryptosapiens/leaderboard

show_title: GM Farcaster ep203 Thursday January 16, 2025 with @humpty and @sahil
text:
Introducing Token Links

Try it now: $degen, $tn100x, $higher, $moxie, $anon

- Mention a token with a leading $, it turns into a link
- Tap link to see top tokens by market cap and recent casts
- Links to Dexscreener and copy contract address
- Working in casts and profiles
- Already on the protocol; just enriching text in casts

Future ideas
- Smarter algo for casts (expect a bit of spam this week)
- Additional info and metrics for traders
- Farcaster social graph signals
- Customization for token creators
- Tie-in with frames and onchain transactions

Known issues
- If token links aren't linkifying, update your app and restart 1-2x
- Casts are slow to load; making that faster
- Token links don't work in DCs or the composer yet
- Sorting by market cap may result in non-FC native assets ahead of FC-native ones, e.g. $anon

Reminder: you can mute all token links by adding $ to your mute words on Warpcast

show_title: GM Farcaster ep203 Thursday January 16, 2025 with @humpty and @sahil
text:
summary of what i'm hearing from builders about the mini-app platforms...

- farcaster: big upgrade in dev experience with frames v2, seeing strong retention w/ improved discoverability, notifs performing crazy well, but obvs limited audience.
- worldcoin: user numbers are attractive, but meaningful lift to adapt product for the platform and actual usage / engagement underwhelming.
- telegram: still king with massive audience, stars make onboarding / monetizing non-crypto audiences way easier, easy build.

anyone have anything to add or having a different experience?
